gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 108, Knicks 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics defeated the Knicks, 108-104.  Jayson Tatum led the way with 34 points and 11 rebounds for the Celtics, while Kristaps Porzingis added 30 points, eight rebounds, four blocks and five 3pt. FG in the victory.  RJ Barrett and Immanuel Quickley tallied 24 points each for the Knicks in the losing effort.  The Celtics improve to 1-0 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 0-1.
